Rumi, the 13th-century Persian poet and mystic, is renowned for his profound and spiritually uplifting poetry. His works delve into themes of love, divine connection, and self-discovery. Here is a collection of his quotes, each offering a glimpse into his deep wisdom:

1. "Let yourself be silently drawn by the strange pull of what you really love. It will not lead you astray."
2. "The wound is the place where the Light enters you."
3. "Don't grieve. Anything you lose comes round in another form."
4. "When you let go of who you are, you become who you might be."
5. "Yesterday I was clever, so I wanted to change the world. Today I am wise, so I am changing myself."
6. "Let the beauty we love be what we do."
7. "Don’t be satisfied with stories, how things have gone with others. Unfold your own myth."
8. "The only lasting beauty is the beauty of the heart."
9. "Be like a tree and let the dead leaves drop."
10. "When you let go of your ego, you open yourself up to the infinite possibilities of the universe."

11. "The only way to deal with this life meaningfully is to find one’s passion and put everything into it."
